docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:23:Start on the 15Loop landing screen. Briefly show a printed-word-style view, then the four connection labels in the product.
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:41:“15Loop asks a more useful question: which connection is missing? A student begins with a free diagnostic before any parent account or payment.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:45:우리 아이 무료 진단하기 = Start my child’s free diagnostic
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:47:### 0:38–1:04 — The four connections
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:51:Use short cuts from real diagnostic questions:
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:55:3. sentence context → word;
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:58:Keep the progress counter visible so the cuts are clearly excerpts from a longer diagnostic.
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:62:“The diagnostic checks four separate connections: recognition, listening, context, and active recall. It starts with 20 words and can add five focused questions when one connection is especially weak.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:64:### 1:04–1:25 — The result and parent transition
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:68:Show a completed diagnostic result with all four scores and the weakest connection. Show the **부모에게 결과 연결** action, but do not reveal a personal account.
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:72:“The result does not say that the child is bad at English. It identifies the connection to rebuild first. Only after the learner sees that value does a parent connect the result to a child profile.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:76:부모에게 결과 연결 = Connect this result to a parent account
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:82:Show the 15:00 timer, a weak-connection stage first, one correct answer, one missed answer returning after other items, and the completed-word count.
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:86:“Continued practice is measured by 15 minutes of real activity, not an arbitrary daily word quota. Every response updates connection scores, mastery, review interval, and due time. Overdue weak words come first, missed words return after other questions, and unseen words fill the remaining session.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:92:After completing the cloze recall, open the optional sentence challenge. Enter a natural but imperfect sentence. Keep the screen recording uncut while the response returns, then show the `GPT-5.6 evaluation` source label and bilingual feedback.
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:101:“GPT-5.6 is used where string matching is too brittle. The Responses API evaluates whether the learner preserved the target meaning and use, then returns strict structured feedback in Korean and English. The curriculum input is allowlisted, no child identity is sent, and a labeled local fallback keeps the lesson working if the API is unavailable.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:111:“I brought the parent story, learner problem, and product decisions. Codex helped turn them into the bilingual interface, adaptive review engine, data model, authentication, safety checks, tests, mobile fixes, analytics, and deployment. Real use by my child also changed the design: open-ended writing became an optional AI challenge instead of a mandatory burden.”
docs/submission/DEMO_SCRIPT.md:121:“15Loop starts with Korean upper-elementary and first-year middle-school learners. The larger idea is an evaluation engine that learns which language connection each person needs next. Fifteen minutes. Words that stay.”
