docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:25:- Primary audience: Korean upper-elementary students and first-year middle-school students who have weak English word connections, plus their parents.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:27:- Primary experience for judges: the no-sign-up free diagnostic first. Parent connection and continued 15-minute learning come after the learner sees value.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:108:3. The founder story: a father built the product after seeing his first-year middle-school child struggle without early English acceleration.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:109:4. The solution: a low-friction diagnostic followed by evidence-based, 15-minute personalized practice.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:110:5. How it works: evaluation across four connections, weak-link identification, and randomized spaced review.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:126:- **0:20–0:50 — Immediate entry:** open `15loop.com` on a mobile viewport and begin the free diagnostic without signing up.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:128:- **1:20–1:45 — Result:** show how the product identifies a weak connection and explains it in parent-friendly language.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:159:   - the free diagnostic begins without requiring parent sign-up;
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:160:   - each diagnostic step advances correctly;
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:162:   - the result and parent-connection transition are understandable;
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:172:2. Complete the judge route from the landing page through the diagnostic result.
docs/HACKATHON_SUBMISSION_HANDOFF.md:187:- [ ] The free diagnostic works on both target mobile viewports.
